  10:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/ze12a/ze12a.c **** /* Shared UART5 link (through the TMUX4052 mux) and the two GPIOs that
  11:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/ze12a/ze12a.c ****  * select which physical ZE12A module (SR1/SR2/SR3, plus one unused
  12:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/ze12a/ze12a.c ****  * channel) is currently connected to it. See the schematic: UART5_S0/S1
  13:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/ze12a/ze12a.c ****  * map directly to the mux's A0/A1 address inputs; EN is tied to GND on
  14:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/ze12a/ze12a.c ****  * the board, so it is always enabled and is not driven by firmware. */
